# BrowserBase Business Ontology

## 1. Purpose
Define the canonical ontology for BrowserBase so finance, growth, product, and operations can run workflow automation on top of one shared data model.

Guiding principle (Palantir-style):
- Model real business objects first.
- Attach events and state transitions to those objects.
- Expose actions/workflows that operate on objects.
- Enforce data contracts so metrics are computable and auditable.

## 2. Canonical Objects

### 2.1 Organization
Represents a customer account and billing entity.

Core fields:
- `organization_id` (PK)
- `name`
- `organization_status` (`active`, `suspended`, `churned`)
- `created_at`
- `segment` (`startup`, `mid_market`, `enterprise`)
- `owner_user_id`
- `crm_account_id` (nullable)

Derived fields:
- `is_paying` (bool)
- `current_mrr`
- `lifecycle_stage` (`lead`, `trial`, `active_customer`, `at_risk`, `churned`)

### 2.2 User
Represents an end user/operator within an organization.

Core fields:
- `user_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK -> Organization)
- `email`
- `role`
- `created_at`
- `last_active_at`

Derived fields:
- `activation_state` (`invited`, `activated`, `inactive`)
- `days_since_last_active`

### 2.3 Project
Represents a workload grouping for browser automation usage.

Core fields:
- `project_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `name`
- `environment` (`dev`, `staging`, `prod`)
- `created_at`

Derived fields:
- `weekly_active_runs`
- `error_rate_7d`

### 2.4 API Key
Represents machine identity used for API/browser session execution.

Core fields:
- `api_key_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `project_id` (FK, nullable)
- `created_by_user_id` (FK)
- `created_at`
- `revoked_at` (nullable)

Derived fields:
- `is_active`
- `last_used_at`

### 2.5 Browser Run (Session)
Represents one executable browser session/run.

Core fields:
- `run_id` (PK; mapped from `browser_sessions.id`)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `project_id` (FK)
- `api_key_id` (FK)
- `started_at`
- `ended_at`
- `run_status` (`pending`, `running`, `completed`, `failed`, `timeout`)
- `runtime_seconds`
- `region`

Derived fields:
- `is_success`
- `failure_category` (`infra`, `user_script`, `network`, `quota`, `unknown`)
- `cost_estimate_usd`

### 2.6 Run Event
Represents an event emitted during run lifecycle.

Core fields:
- `event_id` (PK)
- `run_id` (FK -> Browser Run)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `event_type`
- `event_time`
- `severity` (`info`, `warning`, `error`)
- `payload_json`

Derived fields:
- `is_terminal_event`
- `event_family` (`lifecycle`, `network`, `resource`, `auth`, `billing`)

### 2.7 Plan
Represents a pricing package.

Core fields:
- `plan_id` (PK)
- `plan_name` (`free`, `starter`, `pro`, `enterprise`)
- `billing_interval` (`monthly`, `annual`)
- `included_run_quota`
- `base_price_usd`

### 2.8 Subscription
Represents commercial agreement between organization and plan.

Core fields:
- `subscription_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `plan_id` (FK)
- `subscription_status` (`trialing`, `active`, `past_due`, `canceled`)
- `trial_start_at`
- `trial_end_at`
- `current_period_start`
- `current_period_end`
- `canceled_at` (nullable)

Derived fields:
- `is_trial`
- `days_to_renewal`
- `is_delinquent`

### 2.9 Usage Record
Represents billable usage rollups.

Core fields:
- `usage_record_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `period_start`
- `period_end`
- `runs_count`
- `compute_minutes`
- `overage_units`

Derived fields:
- `billable_overage_usd`

### 2.10 Invoice
Represents a financial document for collected revenue.

Core fields:
- `invoice_id` (PK)
- `organization_id` (FK)
- `subscription_id` (FK)
- `invoice_status` (`draft`, `open`, `paid`, `void`, `uncollectible`)
- `issued_at`
- `due_at`
- `paid_at` (nullable)
- `amount_due_usd`
- `amount_paid_usd`

Derived fields:
- `days_past_due`
- `collection_state` (`current`, `grace`, `dunning`, `write_off`)

